-Correct.

17:17.400 --> 17:18.900
[Judy] Did you get
a response from him?

17:18.967 --> 17:20.033
No response at all.

17:20.100 --> 17:21.533
And you didn't go
over the next day?

17:21.600 --> 17:24.266
No, well, I passed by
and his car wasn't there

17:24.333 --> 17:25.533
at that time. I knew
that he wasn't home,

17:25.600 --> 17:27.100
so I didn't bother to
get off or anything.

17:27.166 --> 17:29.667
Okay, and did you at some point

17:29.734 --> 17:31.433
block him from
communicating with you?

17:31.500 --> 17:32.967
-At some point, I did.
-Just a second.

17:33.033 --> 17:34.433
At what point on what day?

17:34.500 --> 17:35.667
May 8th.

17:35.734 --> 17:37.934
[Judy] And tell me why you
blocked him on May 8th.

17:38.000 --> 17:41.767
I was texting and calling Steve,

17:41.834 --> 17:44.734
Steve had let me know that
he was gonna reach out to him.

17:44.800 --> 17:48.100
I had let Steve know,
keep me out of this.

17:48.166 --> 17:49.600
[Judy] Well, you hadn't
had a fight with him?

17:49.667 --> 17:50.633
No.

17:50.700 --> 17:52.567
So why wouldn't you just
give him back his mic?

17:52.633 --> 17:54.867
What were you dealing
with Steve for?

17:54.934 --> 17:55.900
I was dealing with Steve,

17:55.967 --> 17:57.834
because I asked him
for some advice.

17:57.900 --> 17:58.934
Steve was already
letting me know that--

17:59.000 --> 18:00.100
Just a second.

18:00.166 --> 18:02.700
-But this is what I don't understand.
-Yeah.

18:02.767 --> 18:07.233
Clearly Steve knew
that it was his mic.

18:07.300 --> 18:08.266
Yes.

18:08.333 --> 18:11.233
Because he gave it back
to him at some point,

18:11.300 --> 18:13.000
so he knew that it was his mic.

18:13.066 --> 18:14.900
-You knew that it was his mic.
-Yes.

18:14.967 --> 18:16.266
So why didn't you just--

18:16.333 --> 18:18.600
And you hadn't had an argument
with him, Mr. Martinez?

18:18.667 --> 18:20.033
[Danny] Yes.

18:20.100 --> 18:25.166
So I'm not figuring out why
you asked Steve for advice,

18:25.233 --> 18:28.166
instead of just on May 5th,
saying, "You know what,

18:28.233 --> 18:30.033
we're not gonna be
home on May 5th,

18:30.100 --> 18:32.567
I'll leave your
mic on the porch,

18:32.633 --> 18:34.033
I'll leave it in the backyard."

18:34.100 --> 18:35.867
There's a piece
missing here for me.

18:35.934 --> 18:40.166
Yeah, it's 'cause Steve was
telling me to ignore him.

18:40.233 --> 18:42.400
-He was telling me--
-Oh, well, wait just a second.

18:42.467 --> 18:44.767
Steve was telling
you to ignore him?

18:44.834 --> 18:45.767
[Danny] Yes.

18:45.834 --> 18:49.600
I'm just curious as to why
you would listen to that?

18:49.667 --> 18:51.266
Because I trusted Steve, I trusted him

18:51.333 --> 18:53.300
-and that's where I made a mistake.
-Just-- Just--

18:53.367 --> 18:55.333
-[Judy] Well, then, it's your mistake.
-Yeah.

18:55.400 --> 18:57.567
Because I'm not hearing anything
that would suggest

18:57.633 --> 18:59.800
that what he was asking
for was unreasonable.

18:59.867 --> 19:02.734
He left a piece of valuable
equipment at your house,

19:02.800 --> 19:04.533
you knew it belonged to him, he said,

19:04.600 --> 19:07.266
"I'll come by and pick it up,"
nothing bad about it.

19:07.333 --> 19:10.800
You don't respond to him,
you block him from your Instagram.

19:10.867 --> 19:14.900
I mean, the smart thing to do,
Mr. Alvarez,

19:14.967 --> 19:16.834
-is to take him to court.
-Correct, Your Honor.

19:16.900 --> 19:18.100
You know, that's the
smart thing to do.

19:18.166 --> 19:20.700
To go over to his house is
not the smart thing to do,

19:20.767 --> 19:24.600
'cause you know he's
acted like a dummy

19:24.667 --> 19:26.867
by blocking you from Instagram.

19:26.934 --> 19:28.367
Your Honor,
I didn't think there was any,

19:28.433 --> 19:30.700
I mean, there was,
like I said, me and him,

19:30.767 --> 19:32.734
I've met his wife before,
I've met his children,

19:32.800 --> 19:34.500
I mean, there was never any--

19:34.567 --> 19:36.166
Any bad, yeah, he was acting--

19:36.233 --> 19:38.266
Never any bad,
I didn't think anything of it.

19:38.333 --> 19:39.600
I was just trying
to pick up my equipment,

19:39.667 --> 19:41.500
and it was my equipment,
he knew it was my equipment,

19:41.567 --> 19:43.800
he even suggested for me
to buy that equipment.

19:43.867 --> 19:45.066
Just a sec, I get it,

19:45.133 --> 19:47.667
so now I want you to
tell me what happened,

19:47.734 --> 19:51.700
'cause I'm not understanding
this whole business here.

